         <abstract>
            <p>A class of finite element methods is proposed for first order hyperbolic equations. The expository example chosen is of a single equation in one space dimension with constant coefficients. Optimal $L^2$ error estimates are derived for both approximations continuous in the time variable and an approximation scheme discrete in time.</p>
          </abstract>
